<br>
So..selling your account, sharing your password, yes, is against the EULA.  But people do it daily.  Heck, husbands and wives share accounts all the time...and I know from a GM that if it's not causing a problem, Sony will look the other way, because they know if they don't, they could lose 2 players, and word gets out, they could lose a lot more...and their goal is customer satisfaction, not getting everyone to quit playing EQ.<br>
